      "writtenOn": "2026-07-20T14:30:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Added a new file in this patchset CompositeQueryExecution, its a package-private class created per query by CompositeQueryProcessor. It addresses the comment to \"consider static / reduce parameter passing\" in a thread-safe way. fields on the singleton bean would be shared across concurrent requests, so each query instead gets its own short-lived instance holding dataspaceName, anchorName and xpathToDataNode.\n\nThis change drops parameters from 5-6 parameters to 1-2, the ConditionEvaluator lambda is replaced by a method reference, and it caches condition results so duplicate condition cps paths cost one DB query. The processor now only validates and normalizes the query upfront, then creates and delegates to an execution.\n\nAdded a query depth limit of 10.",
      "revId": "3296442d0c73f14d6bfe261b36874cbc5e3f9d33",
      "serverId": "14b4e41f-c4e3-4fb9-9955-6a9b5656895a"
